    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Zagat Chooses Branding Iron</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By STUART ELLIOT</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Zagat Survey, purveyor of information about restaurants and night life, names Branding Iron as its first agency of record (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Zagat Survey in New York, the purveyor of information about restaurants and night life, has named Branding Iron in Irvington, N.Y., as its first agency of record. Billings were estimated at more than $1 million.</p>
        <p>To promote the publication of the 2001 Zagat guidebooks, Branding Iron created print, radio and outdoor ads for five cities: Boston, Chicago, Los Angeles, New York and San Francisco.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Zagat Survey in New York, the purveyor of information about restaurants and night life, has named Branding Iron in Irvington, N.Y., as its first agency of record. Billings were estimated at more than $1 million.</p>
        <p>To promote the publication of the 2001 Zagat guidebooks, Branding Iron created print, radio and outdoor ads for five cities: Boston, Chicago, Los Angeles, New York and San Francisco.</p>
        <p>Branding Iron was started by J. J. Jordan, a former worldwide creative director at J. Walter Thompson, part of the WPP Group.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
